    <div id="column_2">
     <p>
      The Regional and Mesoscale Meteorology Branch (RAMMB) of NOAA/NESDIS conducts research on the use of satellite data to improve analysis, forecasts and warnings for regional and mesoscale meteorological events.  RAMMB is co-located with the
      <a href="http://www.cira.colostate.edu/">
       Cooperative Institute for Research in the Atmosphere (CIRA)
      </a>
      at Colorado State University in Fort Collins, CO.
     </p>
     <h3>
      Current Highlights
